            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-02T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="1611" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.22/8–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-02T19:00:00+08:00">August 2, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 2—8:45 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2990. Siege ConGen building lifted 5:50 p. m. August 2nd Local Standard Time on
                    order General Labor Union following second session <pb facs="1274" n="1264" xml:id="pg_1264"/> with Thomas and Smith this afternoon. Last unauthorized
                    person has left building and outer gate secured. Besieged officers going home
                    for first time since July 29. ConGen plans to open for normal business tomorrow.
                    For details settlement proposed to Navy by General Labor Union, see AstALUSNA
                    telegram to CNO 020940Z.<note n="36" xml:id="d1611fn36">Not found in Department
                        of the State files.</note>
                </p>
                <p>ComMarianas, please pass to Ambassador Stuart.<note n="37" xml:id="d1611fn37">Ambassador Stuart was en route to the United States.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 1670, Canton 936, Peiping 235.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
